      "rationale": "The primary QoIs — volume-averaged scalar shear stress, Lagrangian particle exposure time, and normalized index of hemolysis — are directly relevant to pump-induced hemolysis per established power-law damage models (Giersiepen, Zhang). These QoIs map directly to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1). Gradation 2 achieved."
